       Y'know, it was fun, Rick.
                  Real fun.

15:27.762 --> 15:29.895
         Y'know I-I-I definitely
              sowed those oats.

15:29.897 --> 15:31.030
        But I think you invented

15:31.032 --> 15:32.965
          a little lesson for me
               along the way.

15:32.967 --> 15:34.499
               Living without
          consequences is great,

15:34.501 --> 15:35.901
             but then I started
                wondering...

15:35.903 --> 15:37.302
           what am I living <i> for?</i>

15:37.304 --> 15:38.637
             What am I building?

15:38.639 --> 15:40.639
     If I'm always looking back,
        I'm never looking ahead.

15:40.641 --> 15:41.840
             And then it hit me.

15:41.842 --> 15:44.309
              We are who we are
        because of consequences.

15:44.311 --> 15:46.712
               You can't live
   without consequences, y'know?

15:46.714 --> 15:47.780
                You feel me?

15:47.782 --> 15:49.848
   [ Slurps ] Wow.

15:49.850 --> 15:52.851
That's a beautiful thought,
 Morty, but, uh, no.

15:52.853 --> 15:54.453
There were definitely
    consequences.

15:54.455 --> 15:55.988
       What're-What-What are you
               talking about?

15:55.990 --> 15:57.923
       I mean.
You did everything you did.

15:57.925 --> 15:59.191
  It all happened.

15:59.193 --> 16:00.525
                     No.
  But the -- the respawn button.

16:00.527 --> 16:02.595
             The -- The do-over.
It's not a do-over.

16:02.597 --> 16:04.463
  You just did it.
   Over and over.

16:04.465 --> 16:05.998
            What are you saying?
             W-What did you do?

16:06.000 --> 16:08.333
I think it's more appropriate
to ask what did <i> you</i> do?

16:08.335 --> 16:10.135
You see, Morty, you weren't
  saving your place

16:10.137 --> 16:11.470
   and going back.

16:11.472 --> 16:12.805
   I don't respect
    time travel.

16:12.807 --> 16:15.674
If "Ant Man and the Wasp"
can do it, I'm not interested.

16:15.676 --> 16:17.076
      It wasn't
  so much a do-over

16:17.078 --> 16:18.477
 as it was isolating
  a moment in time,

16:18.479 --> 16:19.745
   splitting your
  probable selves,

16:19.747 --> 16:21.614
and shunting you into
to into a near-duplicate,

16:21.616 --> 16:24.217
equally probable reality,
transporting you into it

16:24.219 --> 16:25.951
    at the moment
of parallel determination.

16:25.953 --> 16:28.553
     Pretty nifty. Time crystals
         are a bitch and a half,

16:28.555 --> 16:31.356
 but the only real hitch is that
         there was already a you

16:31.358 --> 16:32.625
       in each
 probable dimension.

16:32.627 --> 16:34.427
 So we had to solve
      for that.

16:34.429 --> 16:39.698
          [ <i> Screaming</i> ]

16:39.700 --> 16:41.166
                That's right,
              you little bitch!

16:41.168 --> 16:42.902
It's "The Prestige"!
You "Prestige'd" yourself!

16:42.904 --> 16:45.170
                     Rick,
           how many did I kill?
 You tell me, Morty.

16:45.172 --> 16:47.372
Every time you reset
to smell Jessica's hair,

16:47.374 --> 16:49.775
every time you relived
 a satisfying fart,

16:49.777 --> 16:51.576
that's how many Mortys
 you've incinerated,

16:51.578 --> 16:52.845
     you greedy
   little junkie.

16:52.847 --> 16:55.180
                 Oh, God --
      even those times when I --

16:55.182 --> 16:56.782
Especially those times.

16:56.784 --> 16:58.984
 It's over, Morty.
    Feel this.
                     [ Crying ]

16:58.986 --> 17:00.385
    Take this in.
    This is God.

17:00.387 --> 17:02.255
               Wh-Wh-Wh-Wh --
          Why would you do this?

17:02.257 --> 17:04.723
My hands are clean, Morty.
I gave you a choice.

17:04.724 --> 17:06.325
      You could
listen to me explain,

17:06.327 --> 17:08.861
in great scientific detail,
 how it all works...

17:08.863 --> 17:10.061
or you could have fun.

17:10.064 --> 17:11.262
  Did you have fun,
       Morty?

17:11.265 --> 17:12.932
                   Is this
             because of the vat?

17:12.934 --> 17:14.598
 No.
                  I'm sorry.

17:14.601 --> 17:16.135
I'm afraid it's too late
  for that, Morty.

17:16.137 --> 17:18.403
What's done is done,
   but it can end.

17:18.405 --> 17:20.272
 The original split
is still timestamped.

17:20.275 --> 17:22.540
I can make it so those Mortys
never existed at all,

17:22.542 --> 17:23.943
      make them
 purely theoretical.

17:23.944 --> 17:25.344
                  Oh, God.
                What do I do?

17:25.346 --> 17:26.811
 I think it's clear
 you've done enough.

17:26.814 --> 17:29.282
             Tell me how, Rick!
Tell me how I save those Mortys!

17:29.284 --> 17:30.483
      You live
with the consequences.

17:30.485 --> 17:31.817
    Those things
 happened somewhere,

17:31.819 --> 17:33.686
  but you can merge
the probable realities

17:33.688 --> 17:35.621
so that only one Morty
      did them.

17:35.623 --> 17:36.622
                 Just do it.

17:36.624 --> 17:38.223
 Alright, lemme just
    sync these up

17:38.225 --> 17:39.624
  and get you back
 to your dimension.

17:39.626 --> 17:41.560
  Wait, so -- so you're not even
                  my Rick?

17:41.562 --> 17:43.228
    Then -- Then why do you know
               about the vat?

17:43.230 --> 17:44.629
Every Rick has a vat!

17:44.631 --> 17:46.431
                     ♪♪

